<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendi kaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Protection of clients </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Krediidiasutuse klient k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on iga isik, kes kasutab v&otilde;i on kasutanud krediidiasutuse poolt pakutavat teenust, v&otilde;i isik, kes on krediidiasutuse poole p&ouml;&ouml;rdunud teenuse kasutamise eesm&auml;rgil ja kes on selle krediidiasutuse poolt identifitseeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a client of a credit institution is any person who uses or has used a service offered by the credit institution, or a person who has turned to the credit institution with a view to using a service and who has been identified by the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Krediidiasutuse suhted klientidega reguleeritakse lihtkirjalike lepingutega, kui seadusega ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The relationships of a credit institution with the clients thereof shall be regulated by unattested agreements, unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Igal kliendil on &otilde;igus tutvuda k&otilde;ikide k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&auml;rgi kohustuslikule avaldamisele kuuluvate andmetega ja krediidiasutus on kohustatud kliendi n&otilde;udmisel need temale avaldama. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) All clients have the right to access all data subject to mandatory disclosure pursuant to this Act, and credit institutions are required to disclose such data to clients at the request thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Krediidiasutus on kohustatud kliendi n&otilde;udmisel andma talle informatsiooni olulist osalust omavate aktsion&auml;ride osaluse suuruse kohta krediidiasutuse aktsiakapitalis ning krediidiasutuse juhtide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) At the request of a client, a credit institution is required to provide the client with information concerning the sizes of the holdings that shareholders with qualifying holdings have in the share capital of the credit institution, and information concerning the managers of the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Krediidiasutuse poolt sooritatavate tehingute v&otilde;i osutatavate teenuste loetelu, krediidiasutuse ja kliendi vaheliste suhete &uuml;ldtingimused (edaspidi &uuml;ldtingimused), intressim&auml;&auml;rad, teenustasud, samuti k&otilde;ik tehtud muudatused eelloetletus peavad olema krediidiasutuse operatsioonisaalis n&auml;htavale kohale v&auml;lja pandud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The list of transactions concluded or services provided by a credit institution, the general conditions for relationships between the credit institution and clients thereof (hereinafter general conditions), interest rates, service charges, and all amendments thereto shall be displayed in a visible place in the client service area of the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda nende kohta krediidiasutuselt selgitusi ja juhiseid. </eesti>
<inglise>Clients have the right to request corresponding explanations and instructions from the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Uuml;ldtingimused k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on k&otilde;igi krediidiasutuse klientide suhtes rakendatavaid standardseid tingimusi sisaldav dokument, mis s&auml;testab krediidiasutuse ja kliendi vaheliste suhete p&otilde;hialused, krediidiasutuse ja kliendi vahelise suhtlemise korra ja &uuml;ldised tingimused kliendi ja krediidiasutuse vaheliste tehingute teostamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) For the purposes of this Act, the general conditions are a document which contains standard conditions applicable to all clients of a credit institution and which provides the general principles for relationships between the credit institution and clients, the procedure for communication between the credit institution and clients and general conditions for transactions between clients and the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) &Uuml;ldtingimused kinnitab, muudab ja t&uuml;histab krediidiasutuse juhatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The general conditions shall be approved, amended or annulled by the management board of the credit institution. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldtingimustes tehtavad muudatused peavad olema krediidiasutuse operatsioonisaalis n&auml;htavale kohale v&auml;lja pandud v&auml;hemalt 15 p&auml;eva enne muudatuste j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to the general conditions shall be displayed in a visible place in the client service area of the credit institution for at least fifteen days before the amendments enter into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldtingimuste kohaldamine krediidiasutuse ja kliendi vahelistele suhetele s&auml;testatakse krediidiasutuse ja kliendi kirjaliku kokkuleppega. </eesti>
<inglise>Application of the general conditions to relationships between the credit institution and a client shall be provided by a written agreement between the credit institution and the client. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Krediidiasutuses olevat kliendi vara v&otilde;ib arestida v&otilde;i konfiskeerida v&otilde;i p&ouml;&ouml;rata sellele sissen&otilde;uet ainult seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The assets of a client in a credit institution may be seized or confiscated or a claim for payment may made thereon only pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Krediidiasutus on vaba otsustama, keda teenindamisele v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i mitte v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Credit institutions are free to decide who to service. </inglise>
